[The translations were requested of colleagues in Seoul by ProMED-mail consultant, Daniel Lucey, MD of Georgetown University and Jayoung Park. ProMED-mail would like to thank volunteer Korean subscribers for assisting with translations of the daily Korean MOH reports.

Currently, there are 34 cases, defined as people who visited Konkuk University Animal Life Sciences Building after 8 Oct 2015 and subsequently developed fever of 37.5 C [99 F] and a pneumonic pattern on chest radiograph. Clinically, they show fever, myalgias, and mild respiratory symptoms; none have a severe illness. In addition, there are 11 people who are currently staying at home awaiting results of chest radiography.

According to the 3rd item above, the epidemiologic investigation is focusing on the 5th floor laboratory of the Konkuk University Animal Life Science Building, where most cases were apparently exposed to the source. So far, no etiologic agent has been identified. We await further reports of the investigation.

Konkuk University is a private university located in Seoul and Chungju. Gyeonggi Province surrounds Seoul. Chungju is a city in North Chungcheong Province, which is south east of Seoul. A map of the South Korean provinces can be found at http://www.mapsofworld.com/south-korea/south-korea-political-map.htm. - Mod.ML

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3758677,195.]
